Below is some further information:

    1. There are two clients: users and trainers.
    2. Each of these has the ability to log into the website through authentication.
    3. Once signed in, they can see in the front page and the button ‘chat' showing up.
    4. Clicking on chat you see all the messages in which the logged client is involved.
    5. Then, you can click over ‘New chat’ and you are given a form to send a new message.
    6. In the form you have to select the receiver (either a user or a trainer).
    7. Editing and deleting messages isn’t allowed.
    8. You can create an admin user if you want to make these operations.
    9. Upload the project to Heroku


You can have as many columns and tables in the database as you want and you can have more features.

Feel free to lay out the front page as you prefer. 
